        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 5 at 1:24AM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 124 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Boston, or 19 miles southwest of Jasper, moving northeast at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Marble Falls...                   Valley Springs...
Yardelle...                       Western Grove...
Fallsville...                     Crossroad...
Swain...                          Gum Springs in Newton County...
Gaither...                        Carver...
Erbie...                          Upper Buffalo Wilderness Area...
Arbaugh...                        Ponca...
Hasty...                          Mossville...
Boxley...                         Wayton...
Lost Valley State Park...         Low Gap...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
